content: I'm looking for some advice on decluttering my desk and workspace. I've been meaning to get to it for a while now, but it keeps getting put off. Do you have any tips on how to tackle it efficiently? By the way, speaking of efficiency, I've found that setting aside specific times for tasks really helps - like on Wednesdays, I always take 15 minutes to quickly vacuum and mop the high-traffic areas of the house.
